TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$m = random(2,8,2);
$k = random(1,7,2);

$ans = "($k x)/(1-$m x)";

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 16:
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
Find the inverse function (if it exists) of \( h(x) = \frac{x}{$m x + $k} \) .  If the function is not invertible, enter $BBOLD NONE $EBOLD . 
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
\( h^{-1}(x) = \) \{ ans_rule(30) \} 
$BR
(notice in this problem the independent variable in the inverse is $BITALIC x${EITALIC})
$BR

END_TEXT

ANS( fun_cmp( $ans, vars=>['N','O','E','x'] ) );

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 
Start with our property of inverse functions \( h \left( h^{-1}(x) \right) = x \), and substitute \( y \) for \( h^{-1}(x) \) to get \( h(y)=x \). Now, using the formula for \( h \) we get \( \displaystyle h(y) = \frac{y}{$m y + $k} =x \)
and solving for \( y \) yields
$BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \frac{y}{$m y+ $k} = x \)
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ y = x($m y+$k) \)
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ y = $m yx + $k x \)
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ y- $m yx = $k x \)
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ y(1-$m x) = $k x \)
$BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ y = \frac{$k x}{1 - $m x} \).
$BR $SPACE $BR
Now replacing \( y \) by \( h^{-1}(x) \), we have our formula,
\( \displaystyle h^{-1}(x) = \frac{$k x}{1- $m x} \).
$BR
END_SOLUTION

      
